      • resolveContext

        protected Pair<Context,CallerController> resolveContext(java.lang.String contextPath,
                                                        Evaluator evaluator)
                                                 throws EvaluationException
        Tries to find the instance of context denoted by given path. For this, iterates over evaluator's resolvers and "asks" each of them about the context. This allows to correctly resolve specific contexts without explicit schema, e.g. refer to a dashboard component without form: prefix.
        Parameters:
        contextPath - path of context to resolve
        evaluator - current evaluator with resolvers
        Returns:
        a pair of context and corresponding caller controller
        Throws:
        EvaluationException - if no context with given path found among resolvers
